WEBVTT

00:00:59.986 --> 00:01:01.587
[Saetbyeol Daycare Annual Recital]

00:01:01.587 --> 00:01:03.172
I made it on time, right?

00:01:03.172 --> 00:01:05.223
I'm not late?

00:01:06.676 --> 00:01:09.428
What brings you here...

00:01:09.428 --> 00:01:10.638
Woo Joo!

00:01:10.638 --> 00:01:12.890
Come on. Everyone's waiting for him.

00:01:12.890 --> 00:01:13.975
Oh, okay.

00:01:13.975 --> 00:01:15.226
Let's go in.

00:01:15.226 --> 00:01:16.961
I think it's starting.

00:01:16.961 --> 00:01:18.796
Yeah.

00:01:18.796 --> 00:01:20.531
Woo Joo.

00:01:21.565 --> 00:01:24.110
Adorable.

00:01:24.110 --> 00:01:25.611
Oh, you brought your car?

00:01:25.611 --> 00:01:27.329
Yeah.

00:01:41.877 --> 00:01:43.212
Finding a spot was rough,

00:01:43.212 --> 00:01:44.755
plus the roads were packed,

00:01:44.755 --> 00:01:46.609
so I kept worrying I'd be late.

00:02:00.396 --> 00:02:03.482
We will now begin

00:02:03.482 --> 00:02:04.817
the Saetbyeol Daycare

00:02:04.817 --> 00:02:06.652
Little Stars Recital.

00:02:06.652 --> 00:02:08.721
What is it?

00:02:08.721 --> 00:02:10.239
It's nothing.

00:02:10.239 --> 00:02:12.324
When's Woo Joo's turn again?

00:02:13.367 --> 00:02:16.169
He's in the second act.

00:02:17.705 --> 00:02:18.856
Here we go.

00:02:18.856 --> 00:02:21.439
[Episode 10]

00:02:34.205 --> 00:02:40.065
[Saetbyeol Daycare Annual Recital]

00:02:42.313 --> 00:02:43.840
Oh well,

00:02:43.840 --> 00:02:46.016
at least somebody came.

00:02:53.449 --> 00:02:57.286
What a poised performance
from our Giraffe class!

00:02:57.286 --> 00:02:58.329
Up next,

00:02:58.329 --> 00:03:00.581
the cutest little ones,

00:03:00.581 --> 00:03:02.374
our Deer class, are taking the stage!

00:03:02.374 --> 00:03:05.302
Give them a warm welcome!

00:03:14.745 --> 00:03:16.831
Woo Joo's got this, right?

00:03:16.831 --> 00:03:19.183
Of course, look whose nephew he is.

00:03:19.183 --> 00:03:20.810
Look, Woo Joo's the only kid up there

00:03:20.810 --> 00:03:23.111
without a worry in the world.

00:03:42.231 --> 00:03:43.482
Here comes Woo Joo!

00:03:43.482 --> 00:03:45.443
Woo Joo!

00:03:47.086 --> 00:03:49.296
You killed it today.

00:03:49.296 --> 00:03:52.642
You're a total natural on stage.

00:03:52.642 --> 00:03:53.659
Woo Joo!

00:03:53.659 --> 00:03:55.578
This is for you!

00:03:56.829 --> 00:03:58.305
I'll snap one of you two.

00:03:58.305 --> 00:03:59.415
Sure.

00:03:59.415 --> 00:04:01.142
Woo Joo, look over there!

00:04:01.142 --> 00:04:02.059
Okay, say cheese!

00:04:02.059 --> 00:04:03.936
- One, two, three!
- Peace!

00:04:03.936 --> 00:04:05.004
Peace!

00:04:05.004 --> 00:04:06.297
One, two, three!

00:04:06.297 --> 00:04:08.549
Peace.

00:04:08.549 --> 00:04:11.318
I love Auntie.

00:04:11.318 --> 00:04:13.536
What was that?

00:04:14.638 --> 00:04:17.058
I love Auntie.

00:04:17.975 --> 00:04:20.394
You love Auntie that much?

00:04:20.394 --> 00:04:23.106
I love Auntie.

00:04:24.023 --> 00:04:25.291
[Saetbyeol Daycare]

00:04:25.291 --> 00:04:26.750
Hyun Jin.

00:04:26.750 --> 00:04:27.501
Yes?

00:04:27.501 --> 00:04:28.586
Can I get a shot for you?

00:04:28.586 --> 00:04:30.880
No, we're all good. We already got some.

00:04:30.880 --> 00:04:33.424
Nice to meet you. You're so handsome.

00:04:33.424 --> 00:04:36.285
I'm Ga Eul's mom. She's Woo Joo's friend.

00:04:36.285 --> 00:04:39.054
You should get one of all three!
Don't you think?

00:04:39.054 --> 00:04:41.557
Would you mind getting one of us?

00:04:41.557 --> 00:04:42.766
Oh, absolutely!

00:04:42.766 --> 00:04:44.643
I'll take as many as you want!

00:04:44.643 --> 00:04:46.729
Woo Joo, picture time?

00:04:46.729 --> 00:04:48.738
Picture.

00:04:49.398 --> 00:04:51.984
Okay, smile!

00:04:51.984 --> 00:04:54.285
Oh, Woo Joo, you're so cute!

00:04:55.554 --> 00:04:57.348
So cute.

00:05:16.784 --> 00:05:18.219
What's all that?

00:05:18.219 --> 00:05:21.347
Hang on, why are you here?

00:05:21.347 --> 00:05:24.299
Didn't you have your nephew's show?

00:05:25.059 --> 00:05:28.229
It seemed fine without me there.

00:05:28.229 --> 00:05:29.438
What about you, though?

00:05:29.438 --> 00:05:31.106
Why did you come back?

00:05:31.106 --> 00:05:33.074
And what's with the box?

00:05:35.694 --> 00:05:37.571
Isn't it obvious?

00:05:37.571 --> 00:05:39.323
I came to clear out my things.

00:05:39.323 --> 00:05:43.209
You're actually leaving for good?

00:05:43.869 --> 00:05:46.171
I made it official today.

00:05:47.456 --> 00:05:49.792
I knew this was coming,

00:05:49.792 --> 00:05:52.093
but now that the divorce is real,

00:05:54.505 --> 00:05:56.347
it just feels...

00:05:58.550 --> 00:06:00.366
so weird.

00:06:01.827 --> 00:06:02.930
Wait.

00:06:02.930 --> 00:06:05.648
Are those tears?

00:06:08.602 --> 00:06:12.238
Then you shouldn't have signed.

00:06:13.924 --> 00:06:16.405
Don't cry. It's okay.

00:06:17.845 --> 00:06:19.847
Please don't cry.

00:06:22.825 --> 00:06:24.859
Good boy, eat up.

00:06:25.703 --> 00:06:26.704
Check this out!

00:06:26.704 --> 00:06:27.954
So adorable, right?

00:06:29.415 --> 00:06:31.375
Woo Joo, look, that's you!

00:06:31.375 --> 00:06:32.960
So cute.

00:06:32.960 --> 00:06:34.795
Seriously, he looks great.

00:06:34.795 --> 00:06:38.173
You're the only reason
I even have a video of this.

00:06:38.173 --> 00:06:40.926
I couldn't take my eyes off Woo Joo.

00:06:40.926 --> 00:06:42.052
By the way,

00:06:42.052 --> 00:06:44.138
how did you find out about this?

00:06:44.138 --> 00:06:45.681
Se Yeon mentioned it.

00:06:45.681 --> 00:06:48.851
I once went to my cousin's recital

00:06:48.851 --> 00:06:52.187
and was surprised by how many relatives
turned out for it.

00:06:52.187 --> 00:06:54.690
So I figured I'd swing by.

00:06:54.690 --> 00:06:56.734
Besides, a good-looking uncle

00:06:56.734 --> 00:06:58.819
boosts Woo Joo's street cred.

00:06:58.819 --> 00:06:59.822
Right?

00:07:02.698 --> 00:07:05.200
I really appreciate it.

00:07:05.200 --> 00:07:07.877
You're always helping me out.

00:07:09.580 --> 00:07:11.790
You know, hearing that

00:07:11.790 --> 00:07:14.376
actually stings a little.

00:07:14.376 --> 00:07:16.420
What?

00:07:16.420 --> 00:07:17.921
I don't know,

00:07:17.921 --> 00:07:20.591
it just feels like you're keeping distance.

00:07:20.591 --> 00:07:22.343
Between us, a little help like this

00:07:22.343 --> 00:07:24.636
is no big deal. Just let me help.

00:07:24.636 --> 00:07:26.396
It's okay.

00:08:27.850 --> 00:08:30.978
He's really taking all of that?

00:08:34.815 --> 00:08:38.027
That looks like a full move-out.

00:08:41.655 --> 00:08:42.798
Well, yeah.

00:08:42.798 --> 00:08:45.175
With all the years I gave this place,

00:08:45.175 --> 00:08:47.210
this is the bare minimum.

00:08:53.250 --> 00:08:55.018
For real, though,

00:08:55.018 --> 00:08:57.220
you're set on leaving?

00:08:59.205 --> 00:09:01.850
I already told you, it's done.

00:09:02.526 --> 00:09:03.861
Plus,

00:09:03.861 --> 00:09:06.113
I've got a plane ticket.

00:09:06.113 --> 00:09:07.489
Staying here in Korea,

00:09:07.489 --> 00:09:09.774
I'll keep thinking about her.

00:09:10.617 --> 00:09:14.329
Will you really be all right?

00:09:14.329 --> 00:09:15.581
I know

00:09:15.581 --> 00:09:18.049
you still have feelings for her.

00:09:19.334 --> 00:09:22.345
How can you walk away like this?

00:09:24.035 --> 00:09:26.049
Can you tell?

00:09:26.049 --> 00:09:29.018
Oh, big time.

00:09:30.304 --> 00:09:32.105
It doesn't matter anyway.

00:09:33.599 --> 00:09:34.766
She clearly doesn't need me

00:09:34.766 --> 00:09:37.151
in her life anymore.

00:09:38.520 --> 00:09:40.355
That's how it's always been.

00:09:40.355 --> 00:09:43.734
My feelings were always deeper,

00:09:43.734 --> 00:09:46.195
and I was always running after her.

00:09:46.195 --> 00:09:47.696
You've seen it yourself.

00:09:47.696 --> 00:09:48.890
All those flashy people

00:09:48.890 --> 00:09:51.941
constantly around her.

00:09:53.191 --> 00:09:56.397
I doubt she ever felt the same.

00:09:56.397 --> 00:09:58.540
Nobody stays with someone 20 years

00:09:58.540 --> 00:10:00.925
without caring at all.

00:10:04.046 --> 00:10:05.506
Maybe you're right.

00:10:05.506 --> 00:10:07.299
Listen, Tae Hyung,

00:10:07.299 --> 00:10:08.634
when I'm gone,

00:10:08.634 --> 00:10:11.053
keep Filmpluto in good hands.

00:10:11.053 --> 00:10:13.514
I poured my best years into it,

00:10:13.514 --> 00:10:15.999
so don't let it go downhill.

00:10:15.999 --> 00:10:17.893
When's your flight?

00:10:17.893 --> 00:10:19.920
The 13th, evening.

00:10:19.920 --> 00:10:23.232
What, planning to see me off?

00:10:23.232 --> 00:10:25.025
Maybe, if I'm free.

00:10:25.025 --> 00:10:27.152
You're

00:10:27.152 --> 00:10:29.604
surprisingly loyal.

00:10:31.114 --> 00:10:32.491
Thanks.

00:10:32.491 --> 00:10:34.226
I jotted down some stuff

00:10:34.226 --> 00:10:36.286
that still needs covering,

00:10:36.286 --> 00:10:37.454
and put it all in a document.

00:10:37.454 --> 00:10:39.581
It's sitting on the table,

00:10:39.581 --> 00:10:41.689
so check it out when you're free.

00:11:09.160 --> 00:11:10.779
What are you doing here?

00:11:10.779 --> 00:11:12.663
I need to tell you something.

00:11:13.615 --> 00:11:15.450
Word got to me already.

00:11:15.450 --> 00:11:17.610
The divorce is finalized.

00:11:19.329 --> 00:11:21.089
Honestly, though,

00:11:21.707 --> 00:11:23.992
it's like none of this fazes you.

00:11:24.751 --> 00:11:26.795
This was inevitable.

00:11:26.795 --> 00:11:29.330
We haven't lived together in ages.

00:11:30.348 --> 00:11:33.918
I wish I could shrug it off like you.

00:11:35.579 --> 00:11:37.790
The moment my stamp hit that paper,

00:11:38.640 --> 00:11:40.800
reality just sank in.

00:11:43.501 --> 00:11:45.648
This chapter is closed for good.

00:11:48.609 --> 00:11:50.444
Starting now,

00:11:50.444 --> 00:11:52.854
I'm done with Filmpluto.

00:11:53.989 --> 00:11:56.165
I at least owed you

00:11:57.117 --> 00:11:59.527
a proper farewell in person.

00:12:03.378 --> 00:12:05.042
Are you sure

00:12:05.959 --> 00:12:08.202
you'll be fine on your own?

00:12:12.007 --> 00:12:14.225
I'll manage just fine.

00:12:15.385 --> 00:12:16.745
Well,

00:12:16.745 --> 00:12:18.664
two decades together means

00:12:18.664 --> 00:12:21.875
there's nothing left unseen,

00:12:21.875 --> 00:12:23.461
is there?

00:12:26.797 --> 00:12:28.857
Right.

00:12:28.857 --> 00:12:31.351
We both put in more than enough.

00:12:52.062 --> 00:12:53.764
Take care.

00:13:11.650 --> 00:13:13.860
What am I eating tonight?

00:13:13.860 --> 00:13:16.062
My back.

00:13:17.572 --> 00:13:20.126
Gosh.

00:13:20.126 --> 00:13:22.619
I told you to see a doctor sooner.

00:13:22.619 --> 00:13:25.571
It wasn't even bothering me today...

00:13:26.790 --> 00:13:29.701
My nap probably did this to me.

00:13:32.546 --> 00:13:33.714
This is no good.

00:13:33.714 --> 00:13:34.631
Put some clothes on.

00:13:34.631 --> 00:13:36.800
That place by the intersection is still open.

00:13:36.800 --> 00:13:37.618
Get changed, now.

00:13:37.618 --> 00:13:39.553
What? Why would I go there...

00:13:39.553 --> 00:13:42.122
Seriously, Mom!

00:13:42.122 --> 00:13:43.849
You know what drives me crazy?

00:13:43.849 --> 00:13:46.092
Ignoring a problem till it's bad!

00:13:47.811 --> 00:13:49.438
All right, I get it.

00:13:49.438 --> 00:13:50.856
I'll go.

00:13:50.856 --> 00:13:54.067
I'll go to the doctor, okay?

00:13:54.067 --> 00:13:57.280
But it's almost time to pick up Woo Joo.

00:13:57.280 --> 00:13:59.072
Leave that to me, I'll call.

00:13:59.072 --> 00:14:01.733
Just change so we can head out.

00:14:12.736 --> 00:14:14.196
[Woo Hyun Jin]

00:14:14.196 --> 00:14:17.758
[Mr. Doo Sik in Unit 207]

00:14:17.758 --> 00:14:18.947
Goodbye!

00:14:18.947 --> 00:14:20.594
Bye, Woo Joo.

00:14:20.594 --> 00:14:22.387
Bye-bye.

00:14:22.387 --> 00:14:24.699
Woo Joo, did you miss me?

00:14:26.208 --> 00:14:29.478
I missed you so much.

00:14:29.478 --> 00:14:31.322
I think you grew since I last saw you.

00:14:31.322 --> 00:14:33.056
You got heavier.

00:14:33.690 --> 00:14:35.384
Woo Joo,

00:14:35.384 --> 00:14:37.602
how about a day out, just us?

00:14:38.565 --> 00:14:40.889
I want to hang out, just us two.

00:14:40.889 --> 00:14:43.142
Let's go.

00:14:46.931 --> 00:14:49.748
I did some research,

00:14:49.748 --> 00:14:53.034
and it says reading to babies early on
makes them smarter.

00:14:54.669 --> 00:14:56.880
Check this out.

00:14:56.880 --> 00:14:58.340
All right.

00:14:58.340 --> 00:14:59.999
Woo Joo.

00:15:01.092 --> 00:15:03.211
What's your pick out of these two?

00:15:08.350 --> 00:15:09.518
The toy wins, huh?

00:15:09.518 --> 00:15:10.435
- Yeah.
- Oh really?

00:15:10.435 --> 00:15:12.754
Books are still important, though.

00:15:12.754 --> 00:15:13.772
Get over here.

00:15:13.772 --> 00:15:14.689
Leave that there

00:15:14.689 --> 00:15:16.608
and we'll pick up some books.

00:15:16.608 --> 00:15:17.859
Look at you being so obedient.

00:15:17.859 --> 00:15:19.750
Come here.

00:15:21.696 --> 00:15:22.739
Woo Joo.

00:15:22.739 --> 00:15:24.115
Welcome to my home.

00:15:24.115 --> 00:15:25.659
Pretty cool, right?

00:15:25.659 --> 00:15:27.610
Jump!

00:15:30.765 --> 00:15:32.874
That's dangerous!

00:15:32.874 --> 00:15:33.625
It's pretty, right?

00:15:33.625 --> 00:15:35.293
If this drops, it's an ouchie,

00:15:35.293 --> 00:15:36.503
so we only use our eyes, okay?

00:15:36.503 --> 00:15:37.504
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

00:15:37.504 --> 00:15:39.413
So pretty.

00:15:40.157 --> 00:15:41.675
Oh my!

00:15:41.675 --> 00:15:43.677
Woo Joo, you curious?

00:15:43.677 --> 00:15:45.299
Huh?

00:15:49.499 --> 00:15:50.835
Oh my!

00:15:51.685 --> 00:15:53.045
- Woo Joo.
- Yeah.

00:15:53.045 --> 00:15:57.258
Careful. If that drops, it'll hurt,
and I'll have to blow on it.

00:15:57.258 --> 00:15:58.334
Right?

00:16:03.196 --> 00:16:05.398
Watch out, Woo Joo.

00:16:07.868 --> 00:16:11.087
I wonder if these floors are too stiff for him.

00:16:14.066 --> 00:16:17.402
What's with that look? Come here.

00:16:17.402 --> 00:16:19.379
Hey, Sun Woo Joo.

00:16:19.379 --> 00:16:21.406
Seems like my home is a hit?

00:16:21.406 --> 00:16:23.284
Even filled a diaper already, huh?

00:16:24.993 --> 00:16:26.595
Over here, time for a fresh diaper.

00:16:26.595 --> 00:16:29.139
Oh boy.

00:16:29.139 --> 00:16:31.090
You really went for it.

00:16:45.197 --> 00:16:47.017
[Mr. Doo Sik in Unit 207]

00:16:47.991 --> 00:16:49.935
Oh...

00:16:49.935 --> 00:16:51.402
[Mr. Doo Sik in Unit 207]

00:16:53.455 --> 00:16:55.540
This one's called Ruri.

00:16:55.540 --> 00:16:56.499
And her name is?

00:16:56.499 --> 00:16:57.459
Her name, Ruri.

00:16:57.459 --> 00:16:58.668
Ruri.

00:16:58.668 --> 00:17:01.129
Little Ruri was an adorable baby dino

00:17:01.129 --> 00:17:03.840
with a sweet tooth.

00:17:03.840 --> 00:17:04.883
You're adorable too, right?

00:17:04.883 --> 00:17:06.509
- Yeah.
- Right?

00:17:06.509 --> 00:17:07.719
Mama Dino grinned and said,

00:17:07.719 --> 00:17:11.222
"I whipped up something healthy

00:17:11.222 --> 00:17:13.607
just for you today."

00:17:14.893 --> 00:17:17.479
When you huff and puff,

00:17:17.479 --> 00:17:19.439
a hole opens up

00:17:19.439 --> 00:17:20.649
in the great big...

00:17:20.649 --> 00:17:22.275
Cotton candy.

00:17:22.275 --> 00:17:23.489
Right.

00:17:23.489 --> 00:17:26.348
[Temporary housing]

00:17:44.990 --> 00:17:47.118
Look at you ringing the bell.

00:17:59.171 --> 00:18:01.189
I bought Woo Joo some books

00:18:01.189 --> 00:18:03.358
and he loved them.

00:18:03.358 --> 00:18:04.943
Thanks.

00:18:04.943 --> 00:18:06.778
Things were so crazy for me today

00:18:06.778 --> 00:18:09.272
that Doo Sik's text totally slipped my mind.

00:18:10.073 --> 00:18:12.792
At least I got it, so it's all good.

00:18:16.246 --> 00:18:17.989
I should head out.

00:18:21.209 --> 00:18:23.486
Oh, right.

00:18:23.486 --> 00:18:25.714
With her back problems,

00:18:25.714 --> 00:18:28.800
the daycare runs for Woo Joo
aren't possible for a while.

00:18:28.800 --> 00:18:31.469
Yeah, I heard.

00:18:31.469 --> 00:18:33.847
I can grab him after daycare.

00:18:33.847 --> 00:18:37.517
Any day I'm not on set works.

00:18:37.517 --> 00:18:41.512
I'd owe you big time for that.

00:18:42.105 --> 00:18:44.190
She said keeping Woo Joo

00:18:44.190 --> 00:18:46.067
at her house is still fine,

00:18:46.067 --> 00:18:47.318
so after you get him,

00:18:47.318 --> 00:18:50.196
just bring him over to hers.

00:18:50.196 --> 00:18:51.997
Go on inside.

00:18:53.366 --> 00:18:56.110
Woo Joo, I'm off now.

00:19:00.206 --> 00:19:02.241
Bye-bye.

00:19:09.496 --> 00:19:11.634
Are you enjoying your book?

00:19:11.634 --> 00:19:13.310
Yeah?

00:19:14.162 --> 00:19:15.678
Look at you, reading all by yourself.

00:19:15.678 --> 00:19:19.675
Keep reading,
I'll be right back after I clean this up.

00:19:48.848 --> 00:19:51.174
What's this?

00:19:51.174 --> 00:19:53.684
How did he forget to take this?

00:20:10.318 --> 00:20:13.488
Is he even eating properly?

00:20:13.488 --> 00:20:16.065
He's skin and bones.

00:20:52.116 --> 00:20:54.558
Time to put your clothes on.

00:20:55.475 --> 00:20:57.691
All right.

00:21:00.264 --> 00:21:02.403
How handsome!

00:21:11.933 --> 00:21:13.903
Forget it, I'll finish this after I get back.

00:21:13.903 --> 00:21:15.446
Woo Joo, let's go.

00:21:15.446 --> 00:21:17.205
Give me your hand.

00:21:22.722 --> 00:21:23.947
Let's go.

00:21:23.947 --> 00:21:26.461
Let's go.

00:21:26.461 --> 00:21:28.430
Let's go.

00:21:33.760 --> 00:21:35.471
Get in.

00:21:41.558 --> 00:21:42.848
- See you, Woo Joo!
- Bye-bye!

00:21:42.848 --> 00:21:44.229
Say goodbye.

00:21:44.229 --> 00:21:45.603
Say "I'll be back."

00:21:45.603 --> 00:21:46.731
Smile and bow.

00:21:46.731 --> 00:21:48.734
There you go!

00:21:51.486 --> 00:21:53.448
Let's go.

00:21:57.650 --> 00:22:00.328
I really appreciate this.

00:22:00.328 --> 00:22:02.288
You saved me from being late.

00:22:02.288 --> 00:22:04.833
The morning daycare run with Woo Joo
sounds exhausting.

00:22:04.833 --> 00:22:08.040
Yeah, the neighbor grandma has been our go-to,

00:22:08.040 --> 00:22:10.334
but she's out of commission for now.

00:22:10.334 --> 00:22:11.669
But what brought you here

00:22:11.669 --> 00:22:13.421
with no heads-up at all?

00:22:13.421 --> 00:22:14.672
Well...

00:22:14.672 --> 00:22:16.553
My morning freed up early,

00:22:16.553 --> 00:22:18.930
and you're right on my route.

00:22:18.930 --> 00:22:21.554
When does Woo Joo's daycare
ride situation get sorted out?

00:22:21.554 --> 00:22:23.476
Let me take care of it.

00:22:23.476 --> 00:22:24.515
Excuse me?

00:22:24.515 --> 00:22:26.475
No, I'm totally fine by myself.

00:22:26.475 --> 00:22:27.273
What's wrong?

00:22:27.273 --> 00:22:29.532
Just think of it as carpooling.

00:22:36.951 --> 00:22:39.026
Am I putting you in a weird spot?

00:22:39.026 --> 00:22:40.323
What?

00:22:40.323 --> 00:22:43.576
That stings a little, but fair.

00:22:43.576 --> 00:22:44.744
But instead,

00:22:44.744 --> 00:22:47.079
if you need my help, just say so.

00:22:47.079 --> 00:22:49.047
That much is okay, right?

00:22:49.765 --> 00:22:51.083
Yeah.

00:22:51.083 --> 00:22:52.543
I will.

00:22:52.543 --> 00:22:54.390
Thank you.

00:23:03.304 --> 00:23:05.564
Wait, what am I looking at?

00:23:06.252 --> 00:23:08.100
No way!

00:23:08.100 --> 00:23:09.527
What's up with him?

00:23:09.527 --> 00:23:10.607
What's going on?

00:23:10.607 --> 00:23:14.197
This thing we put up today
on the GloMarket site

00:23:14.197 --> 00:23:17.111
was gone within two hours flat.

00:23:17.111 --> 00:23:18.994
For real?

00:23:20.946 --> 00:23:23.491
Manager, did you see this?

00:23:23.491 --> 00:23:24.617
Yes.

00:23:24.617 --> 00:23:27.373
The folks over at GloMarket are loving it, too.

00:23:27.373 --> 00:23:28.996
They just reached out

00:23:28.996 --> 00:23:31.957
asking to lock down a timeline
for the next product rollout.

00:23:31.957 --> 00:23:34.585
Every sleepless night was worth it.

00:23:34.585 --> 00:23:36.174
Thank goodness.

00:23:36.174 --> 00:23:38.531
[Amy Choo's Weekly Routine]

00:23:38.531 --> 00:23:39.905
[Cold Buckwheat Noodles, Mido]

00:23:39.905 --> 00:23:40.739
[Roast and Grilled Meat]

00:23:40.739 --> 00:23:42.350
[Vine Salad, Osaka Tempura Rice Bowl]

00:23:45.572 --> 00:23:47.477
[Don't Forget Her Supplements]

00:23:47.477 --> 00:23:49.729
What's so crucial about this thing

00:23:49.729 --> 00:23:50.855
that he nagged me nonstop to read it?

00:23:50.855 --> 00:23:52.316
So I went ahead and looked it over,

00:23:52.316 --> 00:23:55.111
and is this some kind of transition file

00:23:55.111 --> 00:23:56.690
or a profile on his former wife?

00:23:56.690 --> 00:23:58.401
Found any good locations yet?

00:23:58.401 --> 00:24:00.528
No. I just haven't found

00:24:00.528 --> 00:24:02.822
anything that really speaks to me,

00:24:02.822 --> 00:24:04.115
so I'm still looking around.

00:24:04.115 --> 00:24:06.400
Wait, shouldn't you be leaving now?

00:24:06.400 --> 00:24:08.202
Your BS interview is today, right?

00:24:08.202 --> 00:24:10.213
I know, I'm on my way out.

00:24:11.830 --> 00:24:14.958
You've really made it big,

00:24:14.958 --> 00:24:16.697
photographer Sun Tae Hyung!

00:24:16.697 --> 00:24:18.650
With your name out there and all.

00:24:18.650 --> 00:24:20.051
It's only an in-house publication.

00:24:20.051 --> 00:24:22.180
That's still a big deal.

00:24:22.180 --> 00:24:23.524
Wait.

00:24:23.524 --> 00:24:24.985
Don't you think we should pick up

00:24:24.985 --> 00:24:27.268
something for the manager's farewell?

00:24:27.268 --> 00:24:29.312
That crossed my mind too,

00:24:29.312 --> 00:24:31.654
but I can't figure out what to buy.

00:24:50.123 --> 00:24:52.538
Hand over those vitamins you carried in.

00:24:52.538 --> 00:24:54.256
What?

00:24:57.572 --> 00:24:59.837
Oh, it's you.

00:24:59.837 --> 00:25:00.878
What's up?

00:25:00.878 --> 00:25:02.673
I've got the BS interview now

00:25:02.673 --> 00:25:04.216
and I'll leave right from there.

00:25:04.216 --> 00:25:05.979
Alright.

00:25:09.074 --> 00:25:10.143
By the way,

00:25:10.143 --> 00:25:12.605
what does the manager like?

00:25:14.239 --> 00:25:16.185
What he likes?

00:25:16.185 --> 00:25:18.901
We're picking out a parting gift,

00:25:18.901 --> 00:25:21.489
but none of us know his taste.

00:25:22.193 --> 00:25:25.120
Well, he...

00:25:28.870 --> 00:25:29.885
Leave.

00:25:29.885 --> 00:25:31.797
I'm working right now.

00:25:35.020 --> 00:25:39.009
He's flying out to the States
on the 13th, a night flight.

00:25:40.340 --> 00:25:42.671
Thought you might want to know.

00:25:42.671 --> 00:25:45.310
It could be some time before he's back.

00:25:47.021 --> 00:25:49.144
Just a heads up.

00:25:50.725 --> 00:25:52.603
I'm off then.

00:25:59.513 --> 00:26:01.514
America, out of nowhere?

00:26:16.904 --> 00:26:18.165
Oh, hold on.

00:26:18.165 --> 00:26:20.421
Watch out.

00:26:20.421 --> 00:26:22.382
Even a coffee maker can be dangerous.

00:26:22.382 --> 00:26:24.483
I'll handle that, alright?

00:26:24.483 --> 00:26:25.968
Amy Choo,

00:26:25.968 --> 00:26:27.780
I know you prefer iced stuff,

00:26:27.780 --> 00:26:30.156
but try a hot one once in a while.

00:26:40.646 --> 00:26:42.202
Head in there and take a break.

00:26:42.202 --> 00:26:43.843
Even if it's just ten minutes,

00:26:43.843 --> 00:26:46.513
resting properly makes a difference.

00:26:46.513 --> 00:26:49.704
You need to take care of yourself.

00:27:01.139 --> 00:27:02.167
I spent way too much time

00:27:02.167 --> 00:27:04.428
hanging around Jo Moo Saeng.

00:27:16.771 --> 00:27:19.608
[Amy Choo's Weekly Routine]

00:27:24.652 --> 00:27:27.989
Five minutes in the microwave does the trick.

00:27:27.989 --> 00:27:29.742
Oh yeah?

00:27:31.322 --> 00:27:33.043
Over here.

00:27:46.710 --> 00:27:49.493
You heard the launch sold out, right?

00:27:49.493 --> 00:27:50.966
That's largely thanks to you.

00:27:50.966 --> 00:27:53.181
No way, the whole team earned this.

00:27:53.181 --> 00:27:55.596
Everyone's already gathered.

00:27:55.596 --> 00:27:57.781
- I'll show them the way.
- Okay.

00:27:57.781 --> 00:27:59.725
The interview room is just over there.

00:27:59.725 --> 00:28:01.143
As I said before,

00:28:01.143 --> 00:28:03.771
this is for the BS in-house magazine,

00:28:03.771 --> 00:28:05.522
so there's nothing to worry about.

00:28:05.522 --> 00:28:08.233
Just respond to my questions freely.

00:28:08.233 --> 00:28:10.163
Ready to dive in?

00:28:13.826 --> 00:28:16.164
Let's kick off the interview.

00:28:17.058 --> 00:28:19.614
The global market has always been

00:28:19.614 --> 00:28:21.872
the barrier BS couldn't overcome.

00:28:21.872 --> 00:28:25.462
And Planning Team 3 made it happen.

00:28:25.462 --> 00:28:28.925
Did you anticipate this kind of result
from the beginning?

00:28:28.925 --> 00:28:31.385
I never once thought we would fail.

00:28:31.385 --> 00:28:33.721
People kept telling me it would be hard

00:28:33.721 --> 00:28:35.883
because we had lost the chance before,

00:28:35.883 --> 00:28:38.017
but I saw it differently.

00:28:38.017 --> 00:28:40.474
I was confident
we would nail it this time around.

00:28:40.474 --> 00:28:44.065
That's exactly what we'd hear
from the youngest manager in BS history.

00:28:44.065 --> 00:28:46.069
It must feel so comforting

00:28:46.069 --> 00:28:47.940
to have a manager like him.

00:28:47.940 --> 00:28:49.690
Absolutely, because of him,

00:28:49.690 --> 00:28:52.573
I've picked up so much
and developed a lot in no time.

00:28:52.573 --> 00:28:53.612
That said,

00:28:53.612 --> 00:28:55.792
when he loaded me up with tasks,

00:28:55.792 --> 00:28:58.086
I did hold it against him a bit.

00:28:58.798 --> 00:29:00.498
Right, the GloMarket project

00:29:00.498 --> 00:29:03.247
was your first since coming on board?

00:29:03.247 --> 00:29:05.367
That must have been quite a struggle.

00:29:05.367 --> 00:29:08.881
I'd love to hear how you handled
the difficult times.

00:29:08.881 --> 00:29:10.587
Rather than overcoming it,

00:29:10.587 --> 00:29:12.220
during those times,

00:29:12.220 --> 00:29:14.684
all I wanted was to head home.

00:29:14.684 --> 00:29:16.379
Get home,

00:29:16.379 --> 00:29:19.888
vent about how hard my day was,

00:29:19.888 --> 00:29:22.605
just let it all out crying...

00:29:22.605 --> 00:29:25.864
And weirdly, that would fix things.

00:29:35.571 --> 00:29:37.239
Okay, the next one is

00:29:37.239 --> 00:29:39.662
for Sun Tae Hyung.

00:29:39.662 --> 00:29:43.097
You led the visual direction on this one,

00:29:43.097 --> 00:29:45.678
and people online are loving it.

00:29:45.678 --> 00:29:49.241
From what I hear, you're diving
into another project with BS?

00:29:49.241 --> 00:29:51.170
That's right, I'm coming on board for something

00:29:51.170 --> 00:29:53.092
the marketing team is cooking up,

00:29:53.092 --> 00:29:55.913
so we should have something cool
coming your way before long.

00:29:55.913 --> 00:29:57.889
Photography isn't really my area,

00:29:57.889 --> 00:29:59.094
but the shots you captured

00:29:59.094 --> 00:30:00.679
really struck a chord with me.

00:30:00.679 --> 00:30:02.476
Thank you.

00:30:02.476 --> 00:30:06.480
What drew you to photography?

00:30:06.480 --> 00:30:08.900
Initially, it was my brother's influence.

00:30:08.900 --> 00:30:11.125
He inspired me to grab a camera

00:30:11.125 --> 00:30:13.946
and start shooting.

00:30:13.946 --> 00:30:15.235
After a while, though,

00:30:15.235 --> 00:30:17.797
I walked away from it completely.

00:30:17.797 --> 00:30:21.916
I swore I was done with it for good,

00:30:22.662 --> 00:30:24.582
but part of me still ached for it

00:30:24.582 --> 00:30:27.044
and yearned to come back to it.

00:30:27.876 --> 00:30:30.171
Then somebody shared a thought with me.

00:30:30.171 --> 00:30:32.131
What did they tell you?

00:30:32.131 --> 00:30:34.385
They said to go and confirm it myself.

00:30:35.176 --> 00:30:38.095
Whether I was clinging to regret

00:30:38.095 --> 00:30:41.115
or genuine love for it.

00:30:41.115 --> 00:30:44.735
There are emotions you can only grasp
by taking them to the finish line.

00:30:45.561 --> 00:30:48.397
So I returned to it,

00:30:48.397 --> 00:30:49.812
and everything became clear.

00:30:49.812 --> 00:30:52.534
How deep my passion runs for this.

00:30:53.611 --> 00:30:55.948
Had it not been for that person,

00:30:55.948 --> 00:30:57.861
I likely never would have considered

00:30:57.861 --> 00:30:59.871
touching a camera again.

00:31:10.842 --> 00:31:12.171
Goodness.

00:31:12.171 --> 00:31:14.006
It's been such a long time.

00:31:14.006 --> 00:31:16.577
You moved so suddenly,

00:31:16.577 --> 00:31:19.675
you have no idea how worried we were.

00:31:19.675 --> 00:31:21.260
I apologize for that.

00:31:21.260 --> 00:31:23.327
That's just how things unfolded.

00:31:23.327 --> 00:31:24.725
Is your back holding up all right?

00:31:24.725 --> 00:31:26.379
It's okay.

00:31:26.379 --> 00:31:28.016
When you're as old as me,

00:31:28.016 --> 00:31:31.116
everything starts falling apart.

00:31:32.020 --> 00:31:33.021
Woo Joo,

00:31:33.021 --> 00:31:34.648
come over here to Grandma.

00:31:34.648 --> 00:31:36.876
- Go to Grandma.
- You're so cute.

00:31:37.863 --> 00:31:39.528
Goodness, look at this little one.

00:31:39.528 --> 00:31:44.120
He's completely attached to his uncle.

00:31:44.120 --> 00:31:46.118
That reminds me.

00:31:46.118 --> 00:31:48.245
Can you pull out some diapers

00:31:48.245 --> 00:31:50.289
for Woo Joo before you leave.

00:31:50.289 --> 00:31:51.322
Diapers?

00:31:51.322 --> 00:31:52.666
Hyun Jin mentioned

00:31:52.666 --> 00:31:56.295
she would share the door code with me.

00:31:56.295 --> 00:31:59.715
But I told her I'd ask you later.

00:31:59.715 --> 00:32:02.521
Oh, about that incident before...

00:32:04.208 --> 00:32:07.139
It did come up,

00:32:07.139 --> 00:32:12.189
and it's best not to start any rumors.

00:32:12.189 --> 00:32:15.570
Alright, Woo Joo, come here.

00:32:53.153 --> 00:32:56.074
Handling everything solo must be chaos.

00:33:07.787 --> 00:33:10.708
How am I supposed to wash or tidy up?

00:33:14.293 --> 00:33:16.858
Okay, let's head in.

00:33:16.858 --> 00:33:19.514
It's gotten so late today.

00:33:38.901 --> 00:33:42.442
You were out of rice, so I made a fresh batch.

00:33:42.442 --> 00:33:46.617
Even when things get crazy,
don't skip your meals.

00:33:46.617 --> 00:33:49.245
Woo Joo, open wide.

00:33:49.245 --> 00:33:50.784
That's it, what a good eater.

00:33:50.784 --> 00:33:53.495
Okay, time to dig in.

00:33:53.495 --> 00:33:54.746
I appreciate it.

00:33:54.746 --> 00:33:57.046
It's burning.

00:33:57.046 --> 00:33:58.667
Be careful.

00:33:58.667 --> 00:34:00.669
Here.

00:34:00.669 --> 00:34:04.559
I swore I was done with it for good,

00:34:05.424 --> 00:34:07.342
but part of me still ached for it

00:34:07.342 --> 00:34:09.553
and yearned to come back to it.

00:34:09.553 --> 00:34:11.179
Then somebody shared a thought with me.

00:34:11.179 --> 00:34:13.056
They said to go and confirm it myself.

00:34:13.056 --> 00:34:15.934
Whether I was clinging to regret

00:34:15.934 --> 00:34:18.365
or genuine love for it.

00:34:22.357 --> 00:34:25.201
He actually made rice and then took off.

00:34:44.800 --> 00:34:47.774
Woo Joo, let's eat some broccoli.

00:34:50.181 --> 00:34:52.185
You don't want it?

00:34:52.185 --> 00:34:54.239
Then should I give it to Uncle?

00:34:59.144 --> 00:35:01.821
Yeah?

00:35:03.319 --> 00:35:05.912
There you go, eating so well.

00:35:23.420 --> 00:35:26.308
I wonder if she's been
keeping up with her meals...

00:35:31.931 --> 00:35:33.678
This is the one, right? Your dream item.

00:35:35.472 --> 00:35:38.350
It looks even better on you in real life.

00:35:38.350 --> 00:35:40.560
What are we doing here all of a sudden?

00:35:40.560 --> 00:35:41.561
What do you think?

00:35:41.561 --> 00:35:43.563
Excuse me, do you have this in stock?

00:35:43.563 --> 00:35:45.110
No, no, it's fine.

00:35:45.110 --> 00:35:46.237
What are you talking about?

00:35:46.237 --> 00:35:48.324
It's a housewarming present.

00:35:49.069 --> 00:35:50.487
If you're worried about the price,

00:35:50.487 --> 00:35:51.238
I'll go ahead and get it

00:35:51.238 --> 00:35:54.699
and tear it open myself, so just accept it.

00:35:54.699 --> 00:35:56.573
No, it's not about that.

00:35:56.573 --> 00:35:57.577
It's a safety issue.

00:35:57.577 --> 00:35:59.204
What if there's a fall

00:35:59.204 --> 00:36:00.580
or a crash from racing around?

00:36:00.580 --> 00:36:01.873
When would you ever fall or run into

00:36:01.873 --> 00:36:03.250
something in your own place?

00:36:03.250 --> 00:36:05.413
I meant Woo Joo, not me.

00:36:05.413 --> 00:36:08.004
The moment you take your eyes off him,
he's darting around everywhere.

00:36:08.004 --> 00:36:09.339
Imagine if he tore himself on this.

00:36:09.339 --> 00:36:11.853
Glass like this is seriously hazardous.

00:36:12.846 --> 00:36:14.767
I appreciate the thought.

00:36:16.138 --> 00:36:18.018
What do you think of this one?

00:36:18.018 --> 00:36:19.036
That looks great on you.

00:36:19.036 --> 00:36:20.392
Try it on.

00:36:20.392 --> 00:36:21.393
Should I?

00:36:21.393 --> 00:36:22.352
How about you?

00:36:22.352 --> 00:36:23.607
Spot anything that catches your eye?

00:36:23.607 --> 00:36:25.730
You always like the stuff here.

00:36:25.730 --> 00:36:26.982
I want to browse a little longer.

00:36:26.982 --> 00:36:28.787
Go put it on already.

00:36:48.309 --> 00:36:50.295
Where did he go?

00:36:58.513 --> 00:37:00.424
This would be adorable.

00:37:02.229 --> 00:37:04.477
When was the last time
the two of us hung out like this?

00:37:04.477 --> 00:37:05.770
Tell me about it.

00:37:05.770 --> 00:37:08.614
Even if it's just a kids' cafe.

00:37:09.566 --> 00:37:10.483
Right.

00:37:10.483 --> 00:37:12.789
Is Tae Hyung not at home today?

00:37:14.874 --> 00:37:16.114
We're not staying together now.

00:37:16.114 --> 00:37:17.991
Wait, how come?

00:37:17.991 --> 00:37:19.534
I mean, obviously.

00:37:19.534 --> 00:37:21.790
The renovation is finished.

00:37:21.790 --> 00:37:23.167
Oh, that's right.

00:37:23.167 --> 00:37:24.456
He was only living with you

00:37:24.456 --> 00:37:25.707
while the renovations wrapped up, right?

00:37:25.707 --> 00:37:28.888
You both hit it off so nicely,
I completely forgot about that.

00:37:33.697 --> 00:37:35.322
Are you free tomorrow?

00:37:35.322 --> 00:37:38.553
We've still got one more date to go.

00:37:38.553 --> 00:37:40.347
Let's go somewhere together.

00:37:40.347 --> 00:37:42.432
Who's that?

00:37:42.432 --> 00:37:44.517
It's Yoon Seong.

00:37:44.517 --> 00:37:45.628
Hey, speaking of which,

00:37:45.628 --> 00:37:47.187
how did things turn out with the date

00:37:47.187 --> 00:37:49.314
you had planned with him?

00:37:49.314 --> 00:37:51.191
Funny you bring that up.

00:37:51.191 --> 00:37:53.401
There's still one remaining.

00:37:53.401 --> 00:37:56.048
Have you figured out how you feel?

00:37:56.048 --> 00:37:58.865
It seems like he takes really good care of you.

00:37:58.865 --> 00:38:01.522
I truly appreciate it,

00:38:01.522 --> 00:38:03.954
but it sits heavy on my chest.

00:38:03.954 --> 00:38:05.497
So he treats you well,

00:38:05.497 --> 00:38:08.028
and yet it feels like a burden?

00:38:08.028 --> 00:38:09.072
How come?

00:38:09.072 --> 00:38:11.514
I feel guilty about it,

00:38:12.254 --> 00:38:14.839
and slightly uneasy too.

00:38:14.839 --> 00:38:17.185
I can't quite explain it clearly,

00:38:17.185 --> 00:38:19.348
but somewhere along the way,

00:38:19.348 --> 00:38:20.428
every kind thing from him

00:38:20.428 --> 00:38:22.935
began weighing on me

00:38:22.935 --> 00:38:25.312
as if I'm in his debt.

00:38:25.312 --> 00:38:27.185
That tells you everything right there.

00:38:27.185 --> 00:38:27.898
What are you saying?

00:38:27.898 --> 00:38:31.106
When it's a person you care about,
being kind to you,

00:38:31.106 --> 00:38:33.149
it brings comfort, not pressure.

00:38:33.149 --> 00:38:34.150
However,

00:38:34.150 --> 00:38:36.736
when a person you're not into treats you well,

00:38:36.736 --> 00:38:38.863
it becomes a weight on your shoulders.

00:38:38.863 --> 00:38:40.156
And the reason is simple.

00:38:40.156 --> 00:38:43.129
It's because that kind of feeling
isn't something you can return.

00:38:44.669 --> 00:38:46.041
Even so,

00:38:46.041 --> 00:38:47.998
you should follow through on that date.

00:38:47.998 --> 00:38:50.166
Remember what Tae Hyung said?

00:38:50.166 --> 00:38:51.376
There are emotions you can only grasp

00:38:51.376 --> 00:38:53.806
by taking them to the finish line.

00:39:02.808 --> 00:39:04.535
This house...

00:39:04.535 --> 00:39:07.565
Does this actually belong to you?

00:39:07.565 --> 00:39:09.231
Right.

00:39:09.231 --> 00:39:11.709
It's pretty jarring, to be honest.

00:39:11.709 --> 00:39:14.153
Wait, this taste...

00:39:14.153 --> 00:39:15.879
Are you serious right now?

00:39:15.879 --> 00:39:18.748
What? It's perfectly nice.

00:39:22.786 --> 00:39:25.831
But really, what happened to you?

00:39:25.831 --> 00:39:27.808
You were always so passionate about decor.

00:39:27.808 --> 00:39:30.144
All that "my own sacred sanctuary" talk
and whatnot.

00:39:30.144 --> 00:39:32.229
My preferences just evolved,

00:39:32.229 --> 00:39:34.898
from idealistic to functional.

00:39:34.898 --> 00:39:36.508
No, you're acting different.

00:39:36.508 --> 00:39:37.776
Other stuff aside,

00:39:37.776 --> 00:39:39.486
when it came to your own space,

00:39:39.486 --> 00:39:40.888
you were crazy about your belongings.

00:39:40.888 --> 00:39:41.680
That's what I'm saying.

00:39:41.680 --> 00:39:43.324
Back at the mall,

00:39:43.324 --> 00:39:46.910
you skipped right past your own stuff
and only checked out baby outfits.

00:39:46.910 --> 00:39:49.538
You're like a whole different person.

00:39:49.538 --> 00:39:51.623
Oh, stop it.

00:39:51.623 --> 00:39:53.375
Hey, what about getting a fountain pen

00:39:53.375 --> 00:39:54.877
as a farewell present for the manager?

00:39:54.877 --> 00:39:56.340
A fountain pen.

00:39:56.340 --> 00:39:57.571
That's a pretty standard pick.

00:39:57.571 --> 00:39:58.589
Hold on, why is he quitting?

00:39:58.589 --> 00:40:00.341
The manager is resigning?

00:40:00.341 --> 00:40:01.867
Isn't he Amy Choo's husband?

00:40:01.867 --> 00:40:05.137
Actually, he's her ex-husband now.

00:40:05.137 --> 00:40:06.263
The two of them split up.

00:40:06.263 --> 00:40:08.015
So he stepped away from work as well.

00:40:08.015 --> 00:40:10.392
Your workplace must be tense right now.

00:40:10.392 --> 00:40:12.463
I expected that too,

00:40:12.463 --> 00:40:13.979
but to my surprise,

00:40:13.979 --> 00:40:15.439
she appears completely unbothered.

00:40:15.439 --> 00:40:17.599
She genuinely seems to be doing well.

00:40:18.609 --> 00:40:22.478
She could just be putting on a brave face
from the surface.

00:40:23.096 --> 00:40:25.240
True, that's possible.

00:40:25.240 --> 00:40:27.242
Honestly, seeing the two of them

00:40:27.242 --> 00:40:29.244
drives me crazy.

00:40:29.244 --> 00:40:32.689
The manager obviously still cares about her.

00:40:32.689 --> 00:40:34.875
If his feelings were that strong,
why did he walk away, you know?

00:40:34.875 --> 00:40:37.044
He should have pleaded, "Pay attention to me.

00:40:37.044 --> 00:40:38.587
I need to stay close to you."

00:40:38.587 --> 00:40:39.824
He should have fought for her,

00:40:39.824 --> 00:40:41.914
instead of leaving.

00:40:43.659 --> 00:40:45.826
He likely thought his presence

00:40:45.826 --> 00:40:48.624
would only make things worse.

00:40:48.624 --> 00:40:50.182
That's exactly the problem.

00:40:50.182 --> 00:40:53.126
Why does he make that call by himself
without consulting anyone?

00:40:53.126 --> 00:40:55.854
They need to talk it out.

00:40:55.854 --> 00:40:58.257
And having family around

00:40:58.257 --> 00:41:00.217
is a hundred times better than not.

00:41:00.217 --> 00:41:01.860
Seung Taek has a point there.

00:41:01.860 --> 00:41:04.071
It's not about what you can do.

00:41:04.071 --> 00:41:06.223
Simply showing up means everything.

00:41:06.223 --> 00:41:07.783
That's the whole point of family.

00:41:07.783 --> 00:41:09.326
As you go through life,

00:41:09.326 --> 00:41:12.702
very few people actually feel
like real family to you.

00:41:12.702 --> 00:41:15.165
If you find someone like that,
hold on to them no matter what.

00:41:15.165 --> 00:41:17.217
My thoughts exactly.

00:41:18.000 --> 00:41:19.002
I just hope she would

00:41:19.002 --> 00:41:21.579
make an effort to keep the manager.

00:41:34.852 --> 00:41:38.313
He's flying out to the States
on the 13th, a night flight.

00:41:38.313 --> 00:41:40.973
It could be some time before he's back.

00:41:49.929 --> 00:41:53.820
How could you wait until now to say that?

00:41:54.746 --> 00:41:56.331
Okay, I hear you.

00:41:56.331 --> 00:41:57.916
I just got to work,

00:41:57.916 --> 00:42:00.127
so I'll look into it and get back to you.

00:42:00.127 --> 00:42:02.379
Got it.

00:42:02.379 --> 00:42:05.240
Should've told me sooner if it was this urgent.

00:42:05.240 --> 00:42:08.413
Of all days, on my precious weekend.

00:42:15.834 --> 00:42:17.978
What brings you here on a weekend?

00:42:17.978 --> 00:42:20.731
A last-minute meeting popped up.

00:42:20.731 --> 00:42:21.968
What about you?

00:42:21.968 --> 00:42:25.268
I had an emergency situation as well.

00:42:27.613 --> 00:42:29.640
Well...

00:42:29.640 --> 00:42:31.941
Have you looked up at the sky today?

00:42:33.226 --> 00:42:35.481
It's absolutely gorgeous out.

00:42:37.059 --> 00:42:38.398
Why on earth

00:42:38.398 --> 00:42:41.320
do we have to be working on such a perfect day?

00:42:45.364 --> 00:42:46.465
- Yeah.
- Hey.

00:42:46.465 --> 00:42:48.509
When does the manager's plane leave?

00:42:48.509 --> 00:42:50.585
It's an evening flight.

00:42:52.204 --> 00:42:55.707
Every flight to the States goes out at night.

00:42:55.707 --> 00:42:56.792
Right.

00:42:56.792 --> 00:42:58.543
After I wrap up the meeting,
I'll swing by the studio

00:42:58.543 --> 00:43:00.506
and leave right after.

00:43:01.311 --> 00:43:04.049
I need to arrive with extra time
to drop off my luggage.

00:43:04.049 --> 00:43:05.192
The States?

00:43:05.192 --> 00:43:07.736
So will there be enough time
to pick up a present?

00:43:07.736 --> 00:43:09.196
I checked and there's a shop

00:43:09.196 --> 00:43:10.881
that carries fountain pens.

00:43:10.881 --> 00:43:13.775
I'll just buy it there on the way.

00:43:18.981 --> 00:43:22.275
Is he moving there for good?

00:43:22.275 --> 00:43:24.405
In the U.S.?

00:43:26.655 --> 00:43:28.364
It's Uncle!

00:43:28.364 --> 00:43:30.708
There's Uncle!

00:43:32.511 --> 00:43:33.781
Uncle!

00:43:33.781 --> 00:43:35.572
It's Uncle!

00:43:35.572 --> 00:43:38.508
- Uncle!
- Uncle!

00:43:39.197 --> 00:43:40.352
Uncle.

00:43:40.352 --> 00:43:42.813
Have you been good?

00:43:42.813 --> 00:43:45.806
- Uncle.
- Uncle.

00:43:50.237 --> 00:43:52.688
Congrats on your first day of school.

00:43:54.025 --> 00:43:56.359
Seo Yoon, this is what you wished for?

00:43:57.703 --> 00:43:59.445
Chan Woo, it's for you.

00:44:01.150 --> 00:44:03.157
And lastly, here you go.

00:44:04.359 --> 00:44:06.169
You must be so busy.

00:44:06.169 --> 00:44:07.988
You don't have to come every time.

00:44:07.988 --> 00:44:10.048
Oh, please don't talk like that.

00:44:10.048 --> 00:44:11.508
I'm not busy at all.

00:44:11.508 --> 00:44:13.427
I'm just grateful, that's all.

00:44:13.427 --> 00:44:17.004
And who might this be?

00:44:18.383 --> 00:44:22.019
Hello. I went to school with Yoon Seong.

00:44:22.019 --> 00:44:24.855
And now we're at the same company.

00:44:24.855 --> 00:44:27.181
Oh, I see.

00:44:27.774 --> 00:44:30.819
You two have quite the history together.

00:44:30.819 --> 00:44:32.321
I appreciate you being here.

00:44:32.321 --> 00:44:34.197
Have the kids had anything to eat?

00:44:34.197 --> 00:44:35.574
Not yet.

00:44:35.574 --> 00:44:37.075
They've been counting down to this

00:44:37.075 --> 00:44:38.727
for the past few days.

00:44:38.727 --> 00:44:40.370
- Pizza, chicken!
- Pizza, chicken!

00:44:40.370 --> 00:44:45.000
- Chicken, chicken!
- Chicken, chicken!

00:44:45.000 --> 00:44:47.377
- Thank you for the food.
- Thank you for the food.

00:44:47.377 --> 00:44:49.161
Enjoy.

00:44:50.756 --> 00:44:52.827
I thought you'd cook for them.

00:44:52.827 --> 00:44:54.496
I gave it a shot before,

00:44:54.496 --> 00:44:55.997
but with children this young,

00:44:55.997 --> 00:44:57.971
takeout wins every time.

00:44:57.971 --> 00:44:59.640
Yeah, that's fair enough.

00:44:59.640 --> 00:45:00.766
Excuse me.

00:45:00.766 --> 00:45:02.754
- Yeah?
- This is for you.

00:45:02.754 --> 00:45:05.711
- You're giving this to me?
- Yes.

00:45:05.711 --> 00:45:06.730
Thank you.

00:45:06.730 --> 00:45:07.799
What about me?

00:45:07.799 --> 00:45:09.758
You don't need milk.

00:45:09.758 --> 00:45:12.388
You're tall enough already.

00:45:14.613 --> 00:45:15.864
Thank you for this.

00:45:15.864 --> 00:45:17.741
It's way better while it's still hot.

00:45:17.741 --> 00:45:19.326
Come over here to eat.

00:45:19.326 --> 00:45:20.327
Have a seat right here.

00:45:20.327 --> 00:45:22.278
Sit down and start eating.

00:45:23.914 --> 00:45:26.500
When you hold it this way,
your fingers don't get messy.

00:45:42.307 --> 00:45:43.433
Wait, what is...

00:45:43.433 --> 00:45:46.052
You finished all of this on your own?

00:45:46.645 --> 00:45:48.271
Oh, you're here?

00:45:48.271 --> 00:45:49.589
Care for a drink?

00:45:49.589 --> 00:45:50.941
I'm good.

00:45:50.941 --> 00:45:52.926
How much did you even drink?

00:45:52.926 --> 00:45:54.861
A bottle or two?

00:45:54.861 --> 00:45:57.138
No, maybe three?

00:45:57.138 --> 00:45:58.238
So what?

00:45:58.238 --> 00:46:00.863
No matter how much I drink, I can't get drunk.

00:46:00.863 --> 00:46:03.611
You look plenty drunk to me.

00:46:04.728 --> 00:46:06.906
That can't be right.

00:46:06.906 --> 00:46:11.243
If I were drunk,
I wouldn't keep seeing Jo Moo Saeng.

00:46:12.472 --> 00:46:15.257
Oh, you're wasted.

00:46:15.257 --> 00:46:17.249
On your feet, let's move.

00:46:18.159 --> 00:46:19.872
For what?

00:46:20.537 --> 00:46:22.238
What do you mean, for what?

00:46:22.238 --> 00:46:24.369
You have to make it to the airport.

00:46:24.369 --> 00:46:26.121
What reason do I have to go there?

00:46:26.121 --> 00:46:28.937
This is all because of the manager.

00:46:28.937 --> 00:46:32.315
I'll drive you, so go after him.

00:46:32.315 --> 00:46:34.116
Don't bother.

00:46:35.235 --> 00:46:37.529
We've already passed the point of return.

00:46:37.529 --> 00:46:40.407
Go catch him before the chance is gone.

00:46:40.407 --> 00:46:42.517
From the moment the manager resigned,

00:46:42.517 --> 00:46:44.619
you have not been the same.

00:46:44.619 --> 00:46:45.995
His absence leaves a hole in you,

00:46:45.995 --> 00:46:48.787
he's constantly on your mind,
and you long to see him.

00:46:49.791 --> 00:46:51.951
So why are you letting him walk away?

00:46:52.610 --> 00:46:55.454
[Amy Choo's Favorites List]

00:46:56.339 --> 00:46:58.174
I came across this.

00:46:58.174 --> 00:47:00.483
He truly understood

00:47:00.483 --> 00:47:03.847
every single detail about me,

00:47:03.847 --> 00:47:06.182
inside and out.

00:47:06.182 --> 00:47:07.684
Yet

00:47:07.684 --> 00:47:09.978
I had no clue about anything

00:47:09.978 --> 00:47:11.929
that mattered to him.

00:47:12.814 --> 00:47:15.724
I never truly gave back to him.

00:47:18.321 --> 00:47:20.771
What right do I have to keep him?

00:47:49.292 --> 00:47:54.355
[Giving Dreams and Love to Children]

00:47:54.355 --> 00:47:56.566
She hasn't been here long.

00:47:56.566 --> 00:47:58.993
She was previously with her family,

00:47:58.993 --> 00:48:00.996
but her mother had circumstances arise

00:48:00.996 --> 00:48:03.656
and left her here suddenly.

00:48:03.656 --> 00:48:06.442
It will take her a while to settle in.

00:48:07.160 --> 00:48:08.745
Even so,

00:48:08.745 --> 00:48:10.747
refusing to eat like that...

00:48:10.747 --> 00:48:14.542
Children who grew up in a home

00:48:14.542 --> 00:48:17.128
struggle the most during mealtimes.

00:48:17.128 --> 00:48:18.630
That's understandable.

00:48:18.630 --> 00:48:22.791
It's nothing like sitting together
around the dinner table at home.

00:48:24.469 --> 00:48:26.378
Ji Ho.

00:48:29.140 --> 00:48:31.501
Ji Ho.

00:48:31.501 --> 00:48:32.852
Why are you out here by yourself?

00:48:32.852 --> 00:48:35.721
I'm waiting for my mom.

00:48:36.481 --> 00:48:40.568
I remember longing and waiting for someone

00:48:40.568 --> 00:48:43.520
so intensely,

00:48:44.382 --> 00:48:46.741
but my expectations were never

00:48:46.741 --> 00:48:48.942
once met.

00:48:53.414 --> 00:48:55.917
[Sunshine Bridge Children's Home]
Everyone's enjoying their food.

00:48:55.917 --> 00:48:56.735
Let's go inside.

00:48:56.735 --> 00:48:58.461
What's wrong? Let's eat pizza.

00:48:58.461 --> 00:48:59.629
Let's go in.

00:48:59.629 --> 00:49:02.372
Ji Ho is here.

00:49:03.030 --> 00:49:04.655
Have a seat right here.

00:49:04.655 --> 00:49:06.335
Here, eat this.

00:49:11.863 --> 00:49:13.759
Did you get something to eat?

00:49:18.273 --> 00:49:22.068
In your opinion, what makes the perfect meal?

00:49:22.068 --> 00:49:25.572
Truth is, I've never been someone
who pays much attention to food.

00:49:25.572 --> 00:49:27.365
To me, a meal was

00:49:27.365 --> 00:49:29.284
nothing more than fuel.

00:49:29.284 --> 00:49:31.186
Frankly,

00:49:31.186 --> 00:49:33.363
I always thought those
who treated eating like some grand event

00:49:33.363 --> 00:49:35.582
were overreacting.

00:49:35.582 --> 00:49:37.699
And yet,

00:49:39.711 --> 00:49:42.005
somewhere along the way,

00:49:42.005 --> 00:49:44.540
I found myself acting the same way.

00:49:45.550 --> 00:49:49.178
When they skipped their morning meal,
it bothered me.

00:49:49.178 --> 00:49:50.805
[You were out of rice, so I made a fresh batch]
When they mentioned running late,

00:49:50.805 --> 00:49:54.258
I'd wonder if they were
taking care of themselves.

00:49:54.934 --> 00:49:58.637
Sitting down to eat together
turned into a form of reconciliation.

00:49:59.528 --> 00:50:02.057
Other days, it brought solace.

00:50:02.984 --> 00:50:05.361
That kind of warmth passing back and forth,

00:50:05.361 --> 00:50:07.688
I believe that's the heart of a meal.

00:50:09.032 --> 00:50:11.534
So the finest meal, in my eyes,

00:50:11.534 --> 00:50:13.460
has nothing to do with the dish.

00:50:14.966 --> 00:50:18.157
It's about the person across from you.

00:50:21.669 --> 00:50:24.805
Here, your friend gave you this.

00:50:30.970 --> 00:50:33.755
Let me step out for a phone call.

00:50:41.258 --> 00:50:42.273
It's me.

00:50:42.273 --> 00:50:43.816
Hyun Jin, I apologize.

00:50:43.816 --> 00:50:45.652
I know it's frustrating to get work calls

00:50:45.652 --> 00:50:46.845
on the weekend,

00:50:46.845 --> 00:50:48.696
but this is really urgent, so I had to call.

00:50:48.696 --> 00:50:49.904
Well...

00:50:49.904 --> 00:50:53.826
That HMR market analysis report you prepared?

00:50:53.826 --> 00:50:55.703
Where did you end up putting it?

00:50:55.703 --> 00:50:58.981
I printed it out
and placed it on the manager's desk.

00:50:58.981 --> 00:51:01.793
Oh, there it is.

00:51:01.793 --> 00:51:03.544
I appreciate it.

00:51:03.544 --> 00:51:05.755
Please say you're not in the office.

00:51:05.755 --> 00:51:08.655
Yeah, I'm pathetic, right?

00:51:08.655 --> 00:51:10.259
Seems like you're outside.

00:51:10.259 --> 00:51:13.179
Everyone's off enjoying life except me.

00:51:13.179 --> 00:51:15.848
One person is even heading to America.

00:51:15.848 --> 00:51:17.266
Who's leaving for the States?

00:51:17.266 --> 00:51:19.894
Sun Tae Hyung.

00:51:19.894 --> 00:51:22.146
Excuse me? Tae Hyung?

00:51:22.146 --> 00:51:24.774
He's your in-law, and you had no idea?

00:51:24.774 --> 00:51:26.776
Oh, maybe that's the reason.

00:51:26.776 --> 00:51:27.902
From what I heard,

00:51:27.902 --> 00:51:30.947
he might just stay there for good.

00:51:30.947 --> 00:51:32.991
Wait a second.

00:51:32.991 --> 00:51:35.493
Is that definitely true?

00:51:35.493 --> 00:51:37.370
What are you talking about all of a sudden?

00:51:37.370 --> 00:51:38.621
I'm telling you, it's true.

00:51:38.621 --> 00:51:40.707
His flight leaves tonight.

00:51:40.707 --> 00:51:42.966
He should be at the airport already.

00:51:52.844 --> 00:51:54.303
So

00:51:54.303 --> 00:51:57.682
how long has this been going on?

00:51:57.682 --> 00:51:58.808
What do you mean?

00:51:58.808 --> 00:52:01.485
Things weren't like this from the start.

00:52:02.520 --> 00:52:05.064
Having feelings for one another

00:52:05.064 --> 00:52:07.074
yet acting like you don't,

00:52:08.359 --> 00:52:10.744
keeping your real emotions locked away.

00:52:13.281 --> 00:52:17.160
That's so far back, I barely remember.

00:52:17.160 --> 00:52:20.580
"I miss you. I'm worried about you,"

00:52:20.580 --> 00:52:23.448
even those basic phrases felt impossible.

00:52:24.208 --> 00:52:26.377
Without realizing it,

00:52:26.377 --> 00:52:30.414
fear crept in.

00:52:31.299 --> 00:52:35.470
So I came up with reasons
over situations that were never real

00:52:35.470 --> 00:52:39.098
and continued shutting him out.

00:52:39.098 --> 00:52:41.350
If I'm being truthful,

00:52:41.350 --> 00:52:44.715
a piece of me wished

00:52:44.715 --> 00:52:46.847
he would stay.

00:52:49.442 --> 00:52:51.611
I believe I get

00:52:51.611 --> 00:52:53.775
what that's like.

00:52:55.890 --> 00:52:58.951
Feeling afraid without cause,

00:52:58.951 --> 00:53:01.003
lacking self-assurance,

00:53:02.542 --> 00:53:06.553
believing you should keep your distance.

00:53:07.627 --> 00:53:09.492
Sun Tae Hyung,

00:53:10.296 --> 00:53:13.457
I let it all slip and I'm paying for it.

00:53:14.942 --> 00:53:17.669
Grab on before it's too late.

00:53:23.810 --> 00:53:25.228
Where did you park?

00:53:25.228 --> 00:53:26.687
What do you want with my car?

00:53:26.687 --> 00:53:27.939
Come on, stand up.

00:53:27.939 --> 00:53:29.774
I told you I'm staying put!

00:53:29.774 --> 00:53:31.067
You should go. Let's move.

00:53:31.067 --> 00:53:32.510
Careful, watch your step.

00:53:32.510 --> 00:53:34.487
Why would I go there?

00:53:34.487 --> 00:53:35.655
Don't look back with regret. Just go.

00:53:35.655 --> 00:53:38.658
And fix your makeup quickly.

00:53:38.658 --> 00:53:39.992
Hey!

00:53:39.992 --> 00:53:43.496
You should've told me I look like this!

00:53:43.496 --> 00:53:44.946
Why are you taking it out on me...

00:53:44.946 --> 00:53:46.207
Get in. Come on,

00:53:46.207 --> 00:53:48.867
Get in. Watch your head.

00:54:11.399 --> 00:54:13.442
Kind of dull, huh?

00:54:13.442 --> 00:54:15.153
Sorry?

00:54:15.153 --> 00:54:16.279
Not at all.

00:54:16.279 --> 00:54:17.780
How about we go in for a moment?

00:54:17.780 --> 00:54:19.532
There's actually something I want you to see.

00:54:19.532 --> 00:54:21.108
Okay.

00:54:26.581 --> 00:54:28.291
I think it's raining.

00:54:28.291 --> 00:54:30.405
Kids, the rain started. Head inside.

00:54:30.405 --> 00:54:31.447
It's raining.

00:54:31.447 --> 00:54:33.286
Let's go inside.

00:54:37.216 --> 00:54:39.510
If it's just this much rain,

00:54:39.510 --> 00:54:41.804
I don't mind

00:54:41.804 --> 00:54:44.881
getting soaked with you.

00:54:45.600 --> 00:54:47.768
I may not be your umbrella,

00:54:47.768 --> 00:54:50.980
but at least until the rain falling on you

00:54:50.980 --> 00:54:52.398
finally stops,

00:54:52.398 --> 00:54:54.192
I can stay by your side.

00:54:54.192 --> 00:54:57.153
What is it? Talk to me.

00:54:57.153 --> 00:54:59.187
I feel safe now.

00:55:00.907 --> 00:55:04.160
When it's a person you care about,
being kind to you,

00:55:04.160 --> 00:55:06.903
it brings comfort, not pressure.

00:55:08.080 --> 00:55:10.903
Hyun Jin, are you okay?

00:55:10.903 --> 00:55:13.406
I have to leave right now.

00:55:13.406 --> 00:55:14.420
Where?

00:55:14.420 --> 00:55:17.089
I'll call you later.

00:55:17.089 --> 00:55:18.758
I'm sorry.

00:55:18.758 --> 00:55:20.593
But

00:55:20.593 --> 00:55:22.711
I really have to go.

00:55:36.461 --> 00:55:38.027
- Let me off here, please.
- Sure.

00:55:38.027 --> 00:55:39.978
Thank you.

00:55:48.015 --> 00:55:49.497
The number you have dialed is currently busy.

00:55:49.497 --> 00:55:51.207
Your call will be forwarded
to a voice message service.

00:55:51.207 --> 00:55:53.401
Fees may apply once connected,

00:55:53.401 --> 00:55:55.455
so if you prefer not to...

00:55:56.904 --> 00:55:58.339
The number you have dialed is currently busy.

00:55:58.339 --> 00:55:59.840
Your call will be forwarded
to a voice message service.

00:55:59.840 --> 00:56:01.342
When are they going to finish talking?

00:56:01.342 --> 00:56:04.720
Fees may apply once connected...

00:56:04.720 --> 00:56:07.848
Who is she even talking to for this long?

00:56:07.848 --> 00:56:08.975
The number you have dialed is currently busy.

00:56:08.975 --> 00:56:11.644
Who in the world is he talking to?

00:56:11.644 --> 00:56:14.550
There's no way he's gone yet, right?

00:56:14.550 --> 00:56:16.389
This can't be happening.

00:56:33.165 --> 00:56:35.408
Hyun Jin, where are you right now?

00:56:43.801 --> 00:56:45.675
Tae Hyung.

00:56:53.284 --> 00:56:54.812
Please stay.

00:56:54.812 --> 00:56:56.856
Don't go.

00:56:56.856 --> 00:57:00.318
How could you leave without saying anything?

00:57:00.318 --> 00:57:02.727
I refuse to send you off this way.

00:57:03.362 --> 00:57:04.946
Wait, you've got it wrong...

00:57:04.946 --> 00:57:06.731
I like you.

00:57:08.737 --> 00:57:10.819
I like you, Tae Hyung.

00:57:12.371 --> 00:57:14.357
That goes for me too.

00:57:14.357 --> 00:57:16.067
Whether you were having proper meals

00:57:16.067 --> 00:57:18.336
or going without food,

00:57:18.336 --> 00:57:20.453
you were on my mind every day.

00:57:21.072 --> 00:57:22.506
The spot where we once shared meals

00:57:22.506 --> 00:57:25.125
felt so hollow without you.

00:57:27.303 --> 00:57:29.754
That's why I kept thinking of you,

00:57:31.307 --> 00:57:33.608
since you were gone.

00:57:36.604 --> 00:57:37.646
Hold on, I...

00:57:37.646 --> 00:57:39.273
Stop. Not another word.

00:57:39.273 --> 00:57:41.383
I understand why you keep me at arm's length.

00:57:41.383 --> 00:57:43.194
But...

00:57:43.194 --> 00:57:46.113
What's a little rain between us?

00:57:46.113 --> 00:57:48.407
Those were your own words.

00:57:48.407 --> 00:57:51.243
You said no matter what,

00:57:51.243 --> 00:57:53.987
you'd stand in the rain with me.

00:57:56.248 --> 00:57:58.283
Nothing else matters to me.

00:57:59.627 --> 00:58:01.629
Why don't we...

00:58:01.629 --> 00:58:04.673
face it side by side for once.

00:58:04.673 --> 00:58:07.792
With you, I feel like I can handle it.

00:58:10.679 --> 00:58:12.511
Because

00:58:13.140 --> 00:58:15.634
I like you.

00:58:23.859 --> 00:58:27.520
But right now, I...

00:58:45.131 --> 00:58:47.007
I told you

00:58:47.007 --> 00:58:49.918
to keep quiet.

00:59:16.078 --> 00:59:18.655
I can't get a single word in.

00:59:19.915 --> 00:59:21.991
I'm not going anywhere.

00:59:23.461 --> 00:59:26.287
How could I leave you behind?

01:00:16.197 --> 01:00:18.280
You're really not going to the US?

01:00:18.280 --> 01:00:21.447
Life without you and Woo Joo
is unthinkable now.

01:00:24.405 --> 01:00:25.905
You like me?

01:00:25.905 --> 01:00:27.216
It's Sun Tae Hyung, isn't it?

01:00:27.216 --> 01:00:29.093
I thought you might waver.

01:00:29.093 --> 01:00:31.113
This stays a secret at work.

01:00:31.113 --> 01:00:34.822
Woo Hyun Jin is my girlfriend.

01:00:34.822 --> 01:00:36.489
[Seoul Family Court]
What is this?

01:00:36.489 --> 01:00:37.572
Hyun Jin.

01:00:37.572 --> 01:00:40.238
Let's just get some good sleep.

01:00:40.238 --> 01:00:41.896
Woo Joo disappeared.

01:00:41.896 --> 01:00:42.697
Sun Woo Joo!

01:00:42.697 --> 01:00:43.565
Woo Joo!

01:00:43.565 --> 01:00:45.408
Woo Joo!